  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries around the world. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key examples include:\n\n1. United States:\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n\n2. European Union:\n- Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n\n3. International standards:\n- FATF sets global AML guidelines\n- Most countries have laws requiring financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n\nThese regulations apply to banks, credit unions, investment firms, cryptocurrency exchanges, and other financial institutions, requiring them to monitor and report potential money laundering activities.",
